<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We may collect information from you in several ways, including:</p>
<p>Personal Information</p>
<ul>
    <li>Account Information: When you register, we may ask for personal details like your name, email address, and phone number.</li>
    <li>Session Information: To schedule tutoring sessions, we may collect preferences such as subject areas, availability, and preferred tutor details.</li>
</ul>
<p>Usage Data</p>
<ul>
    <li>Session Information: To schedule tutoring sessions, we may collect preferences such as subject areas, availability, and preferred tutor details.</li>
    <li>Device and Browser Information: We collect data on your device type, browser, IP address, and how you interact with our site to help us improve our services.</li>
</ul>
<p>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</p>
<ul>
    <li>Cookies: We use cookies to remember your preferences and enhance your experience on our site. You can adjust cookie preferences in your browser settings.</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Provide Services: Schedule, manage, and update you on tutoring sessions.</li>
    <li>Communicate with You: Send important notices, updates, and respond to inquiries.</li>
    <li>Improve User Experience: Analyze site usage to enhance website performance and functionality.</li>
    <li>Personalize Content: Customize and improve the content and offerings presented on our website.</li>
</ul>
<h2>3. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
<p>We do not sell or rent your personal information. We may share your information with:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Tutors: To facilitate scheduled sessions and enable communication about specific sessions.</li>
    <li>Service Providers: Third-party companies who assist us with website operation, customer service, and other essential services. These providers only access personal information as needed to perform their duties.</li>
    <li>Legal Compliance: If required by law or to protect the rights, property, or safety of our company, users, or others.</li>
</ul>
<h2>4. Security of Your Information</h2>
<p>We use industry-standard security measures to protect your information. While we take reasonable precautions, no system is entirely secure. We encourage you to take measures to protect your account information.</p>
<h2>5. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
<p>You may have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Access and Update: View and update your personal information in your account settings.</li>
    <li>Delete Account: Request to delete your account and associated data.</li>
    <li>Opt-Out: Unsubscribe from marketing emails by following the instructions in the email or by contacting us.</li>
</ul>
<h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>Our services are intended for users over the age of 18. If we learn we have collected data from a child 17 or under, we will delete it promptly.</p>
<h2>7. Third-Party Links</h2>
<p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these sites. We recommend reviewing their privacy policies.</p>
<h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. Please review the policy periodically for updates.</p>
